# Eval case: tax-harvesting-advisor

IDEA="Create a local capital-gains tax-loss-harvesting advisor for one Indian retail investor. Ingest broker tradebook and holdings CSVs, compute realized and unrealized short-term and long-term gains under Indian rules, and a deterministic model identifies harvesting opportunities within the annual LTCG exemption. A local LLM narrates the rationale from structured numbers only. Output a Markdown harvesting plan."

CONTEXT="Target: single Indian retail investor, laptop-only, no cloud sync. Stack: Python CLI; Pandas; DuckDB (encrypted); Ollama 8B optional. Formats: 2 CSV templates (Zerodha tradebook, holdings). Limits: max 1 financial year per run; equity and equity-MF only. Non-goals: order placement; broker API trading; tax filing/ITR submission; cloud LLM default; React UI; multi-user; rebalancing automation; derivatives/F&O; sending holdings to any LLM. Defer: debt instruments; multi-broker merge; what-if scenarios."
